            {
                "comment": "Prof Glotzer is a great professor and clearly loves what she teaches, as well as caring about how we do in the class. That being said, the criteria for the papers were hard to follow and would have been difficult for me to finish without any help. The lectures are very useful though and I went back to my notes often. ",
                "difficulty_rating": 3,
                "quality_rating": 5
            },
            {
                "comment": "The notes acquired in lectures and discussions are influential to complete most homework assignments, thus grading is relatively, but fairly, hard. Not much outside work or hardship if you pay attention in lectures, however sometimes they can seem a bit long. ",
                "difficulty_rating": 2,
                "quality_rating": 4
            },
            {
                "comment": "Prof Glotzer was so so knowledgeable and worked hard to make her lectures interesting and relatable. I found her to be very insightful. In my opinion the class was very easy, midterm wording was a bit tricky but graded generously. All other assignments were short and easy, clear guidelines with lots of room to work. Loved her, would reccomend!",
                "difficulty_rating": 2,
                "quality_rating": 5
            },
            {
